# AI Documentation Synchronization

When implementing or reviewing changes, keep AI-maintained docs in sync with the real codebase.

## Entry points

1. **[`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md)** ΓÇö committed bootstrap for any AI agent (on GitHub).
2. **Local `ai/`** (gitignored) ΓÇö full docs; update here, never commit `ai/` to git.

## Covered files (local `ai/`)

- [`ai/PROJECT_CONTEXT.md`](../../ai/PROJECT_CONTEXT.md)
- [`ai/AI_RULES.md`](../../ai/AI_RULES.md)
- [`ai/ARCHITECTURE_DECISIONS.md`](../../ai/ARCHITECTURE_DECISIONS.md)

Also keep this rule file aligned when agent behavior changes.

(`CURRENT_STATE.md`, `TASK_TEMPLATE.md`, and `PROMPT_PATTERNS.md` are not maintained. Do not create `PROMPT_PATTERNS.md`.)

## Update docs when changes affect

Architecture, features, APIs, database models, environment variables, workflows, setup steps, dependencies, risky systems (import/clear data), conventions, deployment behavior, Tauri capabilities, or major refactors.

## Agent behavior

- Update affected **local** `ai/` documentation as part of implementation work when triggers apply.
- **Inspect implementation first** ΓÇö do not update docs blindly.
- Prefer **incremental section edits** over full rewrites.
- **Preserve useful historical context** unless factually wrong.
- Cross-link to [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) instead of duplicating bootstrap rules in committed files.

## Avoid

- Committing `ai/` to git (folder is gitignored)
- Editing stale pointer files under `frontend/ai/` instead of local `ai/`
- Documenting non-existent features without marking them as planned

Full policy: [`ai/AI_RULES.md`](../../ai/AI_RULES.md) (local)
